      <div class="msgContentFrame">Just read this link in another forum and as I'm a one forum guy (postig that is) I thought I'd put the link here and ask the ZAM people to post their thoughts on it. I currently have this trait and assumed (wrongly it seems) that it is active when you are casting.  <br /> <br /><a href="http://www.ffxivcore.com/topic/26578-thaumaturge-tanking/" title="http://www.ffxivcore.com/topic/26578-thaumaturge-tanking/" rel="external nofollow">http://www.ffxivcore.com/topic/26578-thaumaturge-tanking/</a> <br /> <br />It seems that is active as long as you have no buffs on you at all, and can it mitigate 80% damage which is pretty amazing as far as Im concerned.  <br /> <br />Anyone confirm this or have experience with it? <br /> <br />Edited: Just found this link which explains it very clearly: <br /> <br /><a href="http://www.ffxivcore.com/topic/26147-firm-conviction-bug/" title="http://www.ffxivcore.com/topic/26147-firm-conviction-bug/" rel="external nofollow">http://www.ffxivcore.com/topic/26147-firm-conviction-bug/</a> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov  4th 2010  1:30pm by EdyNOTB </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov  4th 2010  1:37pm by EdyNOTB </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179">Loadstone Profile</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649">Thaumaturge Guide</a> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1229110.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
