      <div class="msgContentFrame">Yep it is pretty badass. I use shell/protect as well. The buff is long enough for 2-4 encounters, so (usually) no worries of having it drop mid-fight. You can always rebuff before pulling anyways, then open with a DD spell to proc the defense buff. Same goes for Stygian Spikes .. can last a battle, or just watch it drop off and get a cast in quick. <br /> <br />Had &quot;red&quot; wights tagging me for 46 during a leve yesterday evening &gt;.&gt;  Shadow sickle still hurts lol. <br /> <br />I have definitely moved some things off my bar since, used to be an absorb ACC junky. Still can, depending on how often you cast spells.  <br /> <br />Wish there was an associated buff icon though.  <br /> <br />So Sacrifice is pretty well useless with this then? <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 24th 2010  1:50pm by SpelunkerOne </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1459262.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
